NEET.description: The All India Pre Medical Test (AIPMT) and all the other medical exams individually conducted by the states or colleges have now been replaced by the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test or commonly called NEET, is the compulsory entrance examination for those students who wish to apply for undergraduate medical courses (MBBS), and dental courses (BDS) in all government as well as private colleges in all states of India. The NEET entrance test is conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) and previously managed by the Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE).
